61273.name: Acrobatics
61273.text: Draw 2 cards. If you play both this turn, draw 2 more.
61273.flavorText: He soars through the air with the greatest of fleas.

61964.name: Arbor Up
61964.text: Summon two 2/2 Treants. Give your minions +2/+1.
61964.flavorText: If you can’t outrun a tree, you really shouldn’t be here anyway.

61970.name: Armor Vendor
61970.flavorText: "You look like the kind of person that would buy three sets of armor. One to wear, a spare, and a spare for the spare."

61283.name: Auspicious Spirits
61283.text: Summon a random 4-Cost minion. Corrupt: Summon a 7-Cost minion instead.
61283.flavorText: "I'm not AWE-spicious, but I am a little spicious."

61971.name: Backfire
61971.text: Draw 3 cards. Deal 3 damage to your hero.
61971.flavorText: "That's the last time I let an imp spit gasoline into my car."

61186.name: Balloon Merchant
61186.text: Battlecry: Give your Silver Hand Recruits +1 Attack and Divine Shield.
61186.flavorText: It's a shiny yellow balloon! But it can be popped with a single point of damage.

61616.name: Banana Vendor
61616.text: Battlecry: Add 2 Bananas to each player's hand.
61616.flavorText: There's always money in the banana stand.

61943.name: Barricade
61943.text: Summon a 2/4 Guard with Taunt. If it's your only minion, summon another.
61943.flavorText: The Alliance and Horde join forces to enforce the fire safety capacity.

61132.name: Bladed Lady
61132.text: Rush Costs (1) if your hero has 6 or more Attack.
61132.flavorText: While you were busy learning magic, she studied the blade.

61434.name: Blood of G'huun
61434.text: Taunt At the end of your turn, summon a 5/5 copy of a minion in your deck.
61434.flavorText: An attempted cure becomes disease, blooming and thriving as rot and decay.

61965.name: Bola Shot
61965.text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and 2 damage to its neighbors.
61965.flavorText: On second thought, bolas aren't very good against flying worms.

61242.name: Bumper Car
61242.text: Rush Deathrattle: Add two 1/1 Riders with Rush to your hand.

61503.name: C'Thun, the Shattered
61503.text: Start of Game: Break into pieces. Battlecry: Deal 30 damage randomly split among all enemies.
61503.flavorText: My grandfather's deck has no useless cards!

61226.name: Cagematch Custodian
61226.flavorText: Cleans up after a dust up.

61188.name: Carnival Barker
61188.text: Whenever you summon a 1-Health minion, give it +1/+2.
61188.flavorText: The barking initially confused faire-goers, so he switched to words.

60926.name: Carnival Clown
60926.text: Taunt Battlecry: Summon 2 copies of this. Corrupt: Fill your board with copies.

61581.name: Carousel Gryphon
61581.flavorText: "When does this bird land in Stormwind? I've been flying for hours!"

61254.name: Cascading Disaster
61254.text: Destroy a random enemy minion. Corrupt: Destroy 2. Corrupt Again: Destroy 3.
61254.flavorText: Please keep all hands, arms, feet and legs inside the ride until the monster comes to a complete stop.

61604.name: Cenarion Ward
61604.text: Gain 8 Armor. Summon a random 8-Cost minion.
61604.flavorText: Don't ask about his right hand. He's still growing into it.

61428.name: Circus Amalgam
61428.flavorText: Who needs a petting zoo when you have all the creatures right here?!

60979.name: Circus Medic
60979.flavorText: Just be careful not to mix this with any creepy eyeballs, tentacles, or dark whispers, and you'll be fine in the morning.

61626.name: Claw Machine
61626.text: Rush. Deathrattle: Draw a minion and give it +3/+3.

61154.name: Cloak of Shadows
61154.text: Give your hero Stealth until your next turn.
61154.flavorText: Only worthy emperors can see the cloak.

61176.name: Confection Cyclone
61176.text: Battlecry: Add two 1/2 Sugar Elementals to your hand.
61176.flavorText: "Oh, I thought it was a desert elemental?"

61957.name: Conjure Mana Biscuit
61957.text: Add a Biscuit to your hand that refreshes 2 Mana Crystals.
61957.flavorText: So THIS is why she was AFK.

61297.name: Costumed Entertainer
61297.text: Battlecry: Give a random minion in your hand +2/+2.
61297.flavorText: Just remember not to talk. It breaks character.

61969.name: Crabrider
61969.flavorText: "Now I'm falling asleep and she's calling a crab…"

61679.name: Dancing Cobra
61679.flavorText: Snakes are just tentacles with fangs.

61945.name: Dark Inquisitor Xanesh
61945.text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of all Corrupt and Corrupted cards in your hand and deck by (2).
61945.flavorText: Fear is the mind-killer, and also the name of my wurm.

61639.name: Darkmoon Dirigible
61639.flavorText: "It's dirigible? I don’t even know what diriging is!"

61629.name: Darkmoon Rabbit
61629.text: Rush, Poisonous Also damages the minions next to whomever this attacks.
61629.flavorText: That's no ordinary rabbit! That's the most foul, cruel, and bad-tempered rodent you ever set eyes on!

61677.name: Darkmoon Statue
61677.text: Your other minions have +1 Attack. Corrupt: This gains +4 Attack.
61677.flavorText: As far as workplace injuries go, Silas is protected by his statue of limitations.

61699.name: Darkmoon Tonk
61699.text: Deathrattle: Fire four missiles at random enemies that deal 2 damage each.

61218.name: Day at the Faire
61218.flavorText: Karl knew he would someday regret that turkey leg.

61228.name: Deathmatch Pavilion
61228.text: Summon a 3/2 Duelist. If your hero attacked this turn, summon another.
61228.flavorText: Worth it for the stuffed toy at the end.

61950.name: Deathwarden
61950.flavorText: Ride or die takes on a new meaning.

61885.name: Deck of Chaos
61885.text: Swap the Cost and Attack of all minions in your deck.
61885.flavorText: Yeah, it's chaos, but it's organized chaos.

61587.name: Deck of Lunacy
61587.text: Transform spells in your deck into ones that cost (3) more. (They keep their original Cost.)
61587.flavorText: Voted "Most Lunacy" in Madness Monthly magazine.

60892.name: Derailed Coaster
60892.text: Battlecry: Summon a 1/1 Rider with Rush for each minion in your hand.
60892.flavorText: So long as it doesn’t kill you, it's considered part of the ride "experience."

61846.name: Don't Feed the Animals
61846.text: Give all Beasts in your hand +1/+1. Corrupt: Give them +2/+2 instead.
61846.flavorText: They're still cleaning up the mess from the last time someone fed the basilisk a deep fried candybar.

61133.name: Dreadlord's Bite
61133.flavorText: When it gets too dull, it's more of a nibble.

61963.name: Dreaming Drake
61963.flavorText: Some dragons dream of conquering Azeroth, some just dream of being 5/6s.

61223.name: Dunk Tank
61223.text: Deal 4 damage. Corrupt: Then deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
61223.flavorText: "When I said bring a tank to the dungeon, this is not what I had in mind!"

61262.name: E.T.C., God of Metal
61262.text: After a friendly Rush minion attacks, deal 2 damage to the enemy hero.
61262.flavorText: There are Old Gods and then there are Rock Gods.

61942.name: Envoy Rustwix
61942.text: Deathrattle: Shuffle 3 random Prime Legendary minions into your deck.

61130.name: Expendable Performers
61130.text: Summon seven 1/1 Illidari with Rush. If they all die this turn, summon seven more.
61130.flavorText: When someone gets injured, it's considered performance art.

61462.name: Faire Arborist
61462.text: Choose One - Draw a card; or Summon a 2/2 Treant. Corrupt: Do both.
61462.flavorText: The bad apple never falls far from the treant.

61268.name: Fairground Fool
61268.flavorText: "What did Illidan say when his rocketeer broke down on the Darkmoon racetrack? YOU ARE NOT REPAIRED!"

61263.name: Feat of Strength
61263.text: Give a random Taunt minion in your hand +5/+5.
61263.flavorText: Generally happens right after the airing of grievances.

61968.name: Felfire Deadeye
61968.flavorText: She only shoots people who pet her cat without asking first.

61940.name: Felsaber
61940.text: Can only attack if your hero attacked this turn.
61940.flavorText: Some drivers rev their engines. This one growls all on its own.

61127.name: Felscream Blast
61127.text: Lifesteal. Deal 1 damage to a minion and its neighbors.
61127.flavorText: All the souls start running when they see the felscream truck.

61271.name: Felsteel Executioner
61271.flavorText: "My mom said I could be anything I want."

61202.name: Fire Breather
61202.text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to all minions except Demons.
61202.flavorText: "Phew! That skull has been stuck between my teeth for hours!"

61177.name: Firework Elemental
61177.text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Corrupt: Deal 12 instead.
61177.flavorText: The brightest spark can still go dark.

61674.name: Fleethoof Pearltusk
61674.flavorText: Guest interactions may vary over the duration of the visit.

61643.name: Fortune Teller
61643.text: Taunt Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each spell in your hand.
61643.flavorText: "I see a giant piano in your future."

61151.name: Foxy Fraud
61151.text: Battlecry: Your next Combo card this turn costs (2) less.
61151.flavorText: His other street con involves a druid. He can't pull it off without a plant.

61205.name: Free Admission
61205.text: Draw 2 minions. If they're both Demons, reduce their Costs by (2).
61205.flavorText: "Quick, get in before someone sees you, or worse, someone sees me."

61437.name: G'huun the Blood God
61437.text: Battlecry: Draw 2 cards. They cost Health instead of Mana.
61437.flavorText: All of the other Old Gods used to laugh and call him names. They never let poor G'huun join in any Old God games.

61178.name: Game Master
61178.text: The first Secret you play each turn costs (1).
61178.flavorText: "You hear the mrgrgls of angry murlocs approaching. Roll initiative!"

61958.name: Glacier Racer
61958.flavorText: It’s just not the same without a super suit.

61162.name: Grand Empress Shek'zara
61162.text: Battlecry: Discover a card in your deck and draw all copies of it.
61162.flavorText: So is a Grand Empress an empress that's grand or an empress's empress?

61180.name: Grand Finale
61180.text: Summon an 8/8 Elemental. Repeat for each Elemental you played last turn.
61180.flavorText: Considering all the other hazards at Darkmoon, overindulgent pyrotechnics seem downright pedestrian.

61663.name: Grand Totem Eys'or
61663.text: At the end of your turn, give +1/+1 to all other Totems in your hand, deck and battlefield.
61663.flavorText: Some say it can see straight into the soul of any who dare to read its flavor text...

61606.name: Greybough
61606.text: Taunt Deathrattle: Give a random friendly minion "Deathrattle: Summon Greybough."
61606.flavorText: The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The next best time is when you lose a minion.

61649.name: Guess the Weight
61649.text: Draw a card. Guess if your next card costs more or less to draw it.
61649.flavorText: "And then at the last second, I'll shapeshift into cat form!"

61962.name: Guidance
61962.text: Look at two spells. Add one to your hand or Overload: (1) to get both.

61580.name: Gyreworm
61580.text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, deal 3 damage.
61580.flavorText: This game of ring toss just got really intense.

61189.name: Hammer of the Naaru
61189.flavorText: The naaru wasn't using it. It doesn't have arms.

61192.name: High Exarch Yrel
61192.text: Battlecry: If your deck has no Neutral cards, gain Rush, Lifesteal, Taunt, and Divine Shield.
61192.flavorText: There can be no neutrality in the fight against darkness.

61685.name: Horrendous Growth
61685.flavorText: Stop picking at it! You’re only making it worse.

61944.name: Hysteria
61944.text: Choose an enemy minion. It attacks random minions until it dies.
61944.flavorText: "My mount and I share a special connection. Just not a good one."

61436.name: Idol of Y'Shaarj
61436.text: Summon a 10/10 copy of a minion in your deck.
61436.flavorText: Without a tongue, it speaks in seven. Without a voice, its echo lingers forever.

61136.name: Il'gynoth
61136.text: Lifesteal Your Lifesteal damages the enemy hero instead of healing you.
61136.flavorText: Well, that just sounds like damage with extra steps.

61939.name: Illidari Studies
61939.text: Discover an Outcast card. Your next one costs (1) less.

61948.name: Imprisoned Celestial
61948.text: Dormant for 2 turns. Spellburst: Give your minions Divine Shield.
61948.flavorText: "Look at your deck, now back to me, now back at your deck, now back to me. Who am I? None of your—I'm on a horse."

61959.name: Imprisoned Phoenix
61959.flavorText: It's actually pretty easy to escape chains when you can burst into flames.

61230.name: Inara Stormcrash
61230.text: On your turn, your hero has +2 Attack and Windfury.
61230.flavorText: A fan favorite, Inara is always met with thunderous applause.

61269.name: Insatiable Felhound
61269.flavorText: Back-to-back winner of the annual hot dog eating contest... and the judge-eating contest.

61435.name: Insight
61435.text: Draw a minion. Corrupt: Reduce its Cost by (2).
61435.flavorText: Shouldn't the eyes be facing backwards for insight?

61952.name: Ironclad
61952.text: Battlecry: If your hero has Armor, gain +2/+2.
61952.flavorText: With one inch of clearance, Ironclad proved ineffective against speedbumps.

61690.name: Jewel of N'Zoth
61690.text: Summon three friendly Deathrattle minions that died this game.
61690.flavorText: This coveted gem calls for you to free it… and unleash an inescapable prison.

61676.name: K'thir Ritualist
61676.text: Taunt Battlecry: Add a random 4-Cost minion to your opponent's hand.
61676.flavorText: Something evil this way comes… and it's bringing friends over!

61956.name: Keywarden Ivory
61956.text: Battlecry: Discover a Dual Class spell from any class. Spellburst: Get another copy.
61956.flavorText: She learned exactly one thing from her old man: copying.

61605.name: Kiri, Chosen of Elune
61605.text: Battlecry: Add a Solar Eclipse and Lunar Eclipse to your hand.
61605.flavorText: Now, when the Sun is between the Moon and the Azeroth... that's when you've got a problem.

61620.name: Knife Vendor
61620.flavorText: "They're perfectly safe! These gloves totally aren't hiding any bandages."

61961.name: Landslide
61961.text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. If you're Overloaded, deal 1 damage again.
61961.flavorText: "And they win it by a landslide! Wait, where did all the other racers go?"

61949.name: Libram of Judgment
61949.flavorText: You really can't judge a book by its cover.

61946.name: Lightsteed
61946.text: Your healing effects also give affected minions +2 Health.
61946.flavorText: All the steed, half the calories.

61123.name: Line Hopper
61123.flavorText: There are two things Demon Hunters know: hopping, and cutting.

61191.name: Lothraxion the Redeemed
61191.text: Battlecry: For the rest of the game, after you summon a Silver Hand Recruit, give it Divine Shield.
61191.flavorText: So infused with the Light, he has to wear double sleep masks at night.

61941.name: Luckysoul Hoarder
61941.text: Battlecry: Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck. Corrupt: Draw a card.
61941.flavorText: Always brings his own reusable shopping bag, satchel, barrel, trunk, tray, and fluffy pillow.

61449.name: Lunar Eclipse
61449.text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Your next spell this turn costs (2) less.
61449.flavorText: When the Azeroth is between the Sun and the Moon.

61229.name: Magicfin
61229.text: After a friendly Murloc dies, add a random Legendary minion to your hand.
61229.flavorText: The best part is when he pulls Deathwing out of a top hat!

61169.name: Malevolent Strike
61169.text: Destroy a minion. Costs (1) less for each card in your deck that didn't start there.
61169.flavorText: "I don't know how those got in there, but I'm blaming you two."

61203.name: Man'ari Mosher
61203.text: Battlecry: Give a friendly Demon +3 Attack and Lifesteal this turn.
61203.flavorText: "E.T.C. is sooo mainstream. Have you heard of Blight Boar?"

61179.name: Mask of C'Thun
61179.text: Deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemies.
61179.flavorText: Hide in the mask, but it will wear you. Through its gleaming eye, you shall see true.

61842.name: Maxima Blastenheimer
61842.text: Battlecry: Summon a minion from your deck. It attacks the enemy hero, then dies.
61842.flavorText: Believe it or not, this is only the faire's fourth most dangerous game.

61206.name: Midway Maniac
61206.flavorText: Faire owners hate him! Learn his secrets with one simple spell!

61238.name: Minefield
61238.text: Deal 5 damage randomly split among all minions.
61238.flavorText: Dodge bombs like you're playing Tonksweeper!

61973.name: Moonfang
61973.text: Can only take 1 damage at a time.
61973.flavorText: Moonforehead just didn't have the same ring to it.

61602.name: Moontouched Amulet
61602.text: Give your hero +4 Attack this turn. Corrupt: And gain 6 Armor.

61682.name: Mystery Winner
61682.flavorText: Yeah, but the mystery prize could be anything! Even a boat!

60443.name: N'Zoth, God of the Deep
60443.text: Battlecry: Resurrect a friendly minion of each minion type.
60443.flavorText: It really just wants to cuddle all the creatures of Azeroth.

61642.name: Nazmani Bloodweaver
61642.text: After you cast a spell, reduce the Cost of a random card in your hand by (1).
61642.flavorText: Her first stage name, Ketchupweaver, failed to excite the audience.

61953.name: Nitroboost Poison
61953.text: Give a minion +2 Attack. Corrupt: And your weapon.
61953.flavorText: Pouring iced milk into your vehicle's fuel tank does NOT provide a Nitro boost, but it does go great with your victory cookies.

61584.name: Occult Conjurer
61584.text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, summon a copy of this.
61584.flavorText: Like mirror image, but more secretive and angsty.

61187.name: Oh My Yogg!
61187.text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, they instead cast a random one of the same Cost.
61187.flavorText: Many wonders lie within, but they are not mere toys when your mind is their plaything.

61683.name: Open the Cages
61683.text: Secret: When your turn starts, if you control two minions, summon an Animal Companion.
61683.flavorText: "Coming out of my cage, and I'm dead by turn nine..."

61625.name: Optimistic Ogre
61625.text: 50% chance to attack the correct enemy.
61625.flavorText: "What if this goes wrong?" "But what if this goes right?"

61282.name: Palm Reading
61282.text: Discover a spell. Reduce the Cost of spells in your hand by (1).

61235.name: Parade Leader
61235.text: After you summon a Rush minion, give it +2 Attack.
61235.flavorText: He's always going to reign on his parade.

61700.name: Petting Zoo
61700.text: Summon a 3/3 Strider. Repeat for each Secret you control.
61700.flavorText: Welcome to the petting zoo. DO NOT TOUCH THE ANIMALS.

61225.name: Pit Master
61225.flavorText: If you win your duel, he'll throw in some of his famous Pit Master barbecue.

61171.name: Prize Plunderer
61171.text: Combo: Deal 1 damage to a minion for each other card you've played this turn.
61171.flavorText: But he'll never be able to plunder the prize of a happy childhood.

61622.name: Prize Vendor
61622.text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Each player draws a card.
61622.flavorText: He's just making sure they're real. Authentic tickets taste like strawberry.

61947.name: Rally!
61947.flavorText: One for the squire, two for the gnome, three for the glory, and GO, GO, GO!

61128.name: Redeemed Pariah
61128.text: After you play an Outcast card, gain +1/+1.
61128.flavorText: "Look at this stick. Look at it!"

61305.name: Redscale Dragontamer
61305.flavorText: Sir Finley made this look a lot easier three expansions ago...

61125.name: Relentless Pursuit
61125.text: Give your hero +4 Attack and Immune this turn.
61125.flavorText: If you steal a Demon Hunter's corn dog, you'll get what's coming.

61129.name: Renowned Performer
61129.flavorText: Cutting the assistant in half is the easy part.

61967.name: Resizing Pouch
61967.text: Discover a card with Cost equal to your remaining Mana Crystals.
61967.flavorText: Just don't put a Resizing Pouch inside the Resizing Pouch.

61207.name: Revenant Rascal
61207.text: Battlecry: Destroy a Mana Crystal for each player.
61207.flavorText: Turns out his face really did get stuck that way.

61222.name: Revolve
61222.text: Transform all minions into random ones with the same Cost.
61222.flavorText: "Please don't ride the carousel for thirty minutes after eating. After the carousel eats, I mean."

61585.name: Rigged Faire Game
61585.text: Secret: If you didn't take any damage during your opponent's turn, draw 3 cards.

61884.name: Ring Matron
61884.flavorText: But where does she keep them?

61291.name: Ring Toss
61291.flavorText: If you liked it, then you shoulda put a ring on it!

61248.name: Ringmaster Whatley
61248.text: Battlecry: Draw a Mech, Dragon, and Pirate.
61248.flavorText: His main qualification is that he'll work with anyone. Or anything.

61246.name: Ringmaster's Baton
61246.text: After your hero attacks, give a Mech, Dragon, and Pirate in your hand +1/+1.
61246.flavorText: A mech, a dragon, and a pirate walk into an Old God's gaping maw. The mech was too crunchy, the dragon was too hot, but the pirate was just right.

61839.name: Rinling's Rifle
61839.text: After your hero attacks, Discover a Secret and cast it.
61839.flavorText: This rifle needs a muzzle for its muzzle.

60916.name: Rock Rager
60916.flavorText: Still doesn't understand why he can't beat Paper Rager.

61972.name: Runaway Blackwing
61972.text: At the end of your turn, deal 10 damage to a random enemy minion.
61972.flavorText: It has been 5 minutes since our last Azeroth Racing League violation.

61966.name: Saddlemaster
61966.text: After you play a Beast, add a random Beast to your hand.
61966.flavorText: Seat covers. Check. Racing stripes. Check. Cupholder. Check.

62049.name: Safety Inspector
62049.text: Battlecry: Shuffle the lowest-Cost card from your hand into your deck. Draw a card.
62049.flavorText: "All right, you're good. No sign of safety anywhere."

61589.name: Sayge, Seer of Darkmoon
61589.text: Battlecry: Draw (card, cards). (Upgraded for each friendly Secret that has triggered this game!)
61589.flavorText: There are no secrets between us... or refunds.

61156.name: Shadow Clone
61156.text: Secret: After a minion attacks your hero, summon a copy of it with Stealth.
61156.flavorText: "You thought you were attacking face, but it was me! You!"

61955.name: Shenanigans
61955.text: Secret: When your opponent draws their second card in a turn, transform it into a Banana.
61955.flavorText: It's not personal, it's just monkey business.

61640.name: Silas Darkmoon
61640.text: Battlecry: Choose a direction to rotate all minions.
61640.flavorText: "You might remember me from such attractions as 'Being Shot out of a Cannon' or 'That Carousel Ate My Friend.'"

61306.name: Snack Run
61306.text: Discover a spell. Restore Health to your hero equal to its Cost.
61306.flavorText: "I'll have two monster churros, a combo box of Yogg-Saron, and one of those turkey legs that ate the Silver Hand Recruit."

61450.name: Solar Eclipse
61450.text: The next spell you cast this turn casts twice.
61450.flavorText: When the Moon is between the Sun and the Azeroth.

61954.name: Sparkjoy Cheat
61954.text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Secret, cast it and draw a card.

61951.name: Spiked Wheel
61951.text: Has +3 Attack while your hero has Armor.
61951.flavorText: Great for driving, terrible for steering.

61426.name: Stage Hand
61426.text: Battlecry: Give a random minion in your hand +1/+1.
61426.flavorText: Holds everything himself because people wouldn't stop touching the prop table.

61135.name: Stiltstepper
61135.text: Battlecry: Draw a card. If you play it this turn, give your hero +4 Attack this turn.
61135.flavorText: Circus school was tough, sometimes you had to step on people to make it to the top.

61224.name: Stormstrike
61224.text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Give your hero +3 Attack this turn.

61670.name: Strongman
61670.flavorText: Sure, it looks impressive until you realize it's a barrel of helium.

61168.name: Sweet Tooth
61168.flavorText: He's been eyeballing that ice cream cone all day!

61159.name: Swindle
61159.text: Draw a spell. Combo: And a minion.
61159.flavorText: You know, it's probably just cheaper to find a place that sells the plushie…

61237.name: Sword Eater
61237.flavorText: How tough is he? He eats swords for breakfast! Without any milk.

61252.name: Tent Trasher
61252.text: Rush. Costs (1) less for each friendly minion with a unique minion type.

61635.name: Tenwu of the Red Smoke
61635.text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion to your hand. It costs (1) this turn.

61208.name: The Nameless One
61208.text: Battlecry: Choose a minion. Become a 4/4 copy of it, then Silence it.
61208.flavorText: Used to be called " , the Nameless," but everyone got confused.

61131.name: Throw Glaive
61131.text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it dies, add a Temporary copy of this to your hand.
61131.flavorText: "No, no, I said SHOW me the glaive!"

61646.name: Tickatus
61646.text: Battlecry: Remove the top 5 cards from your deck. Corrupt: Your opponent's deck instead.
